---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<main>
			<section>
				<h1>Network Diagnostic Tool using guide</h1>
				<br>
				<br>
			  
				<h2>üõ†Ô∏è Network Diagnostic Tool</h2>
				<p><strong>Network Diagnostic Tool</strong> is an automated CMD script designed to quickly and efficiently perform common network diagnostics across multiple company campaigns. Its goal is to reduce response times during critical events and standardize the collection of technical network data.</p>
			  
				<h2>üìå Objective</h2>
				<ul>
				  <li>Develop and implement an automated diagnostic tool to reduce response times during critical events across multiple campaigns, facilitating the generation of standardized network logs.</li>
				</ul>
			  
				<h2>üìÅ Repository Contents</h2>
				<ul>
				  <li><code>Network_Diagnostic_Tool.cmd</code>: main script ready to execute.</li>
				  <li><code>README.md</code>: this documentation file.</li>
				  <li><code>/docs/guia_de_uso.pdf</code> <em>(optional)</em>: PDF user guide.</li>
				  <li><code>/logs/ejemplos/</code>: sample log outputs generated by the tool.</li>
				</ul>
			  
				<h2>‚öôÔ∏è System Requirements</h2>
				<ul>
				  <li>Windows 10 or later</li>
				  <li>Access to Command Prompt (CMD)</li>
				  <li>Internet connectivity</li>
				  <li>Does not require administrator privileges</li>
				</ul>
			  
				<h2>üöÄ How to Use the Tool</h2>
				<ol>
				  <li><strong>Run the Script:</strong> Double-click <code>Network_Diagnostic_Tool.cmd</code>.</li>
				  <li><strong>Select a Campaign:</strong> Choose a campaign from the menu by typing the corresponding number.</li>
			  
				  <li><strong>Select a Target:</strong> Choose the destination (URL or service) you wish to diagnose.</li>
			  
				  <li><strong>Run Diagnostics:</strong> The script will automatically execute the following commands:
					<ul>
					  <li><code>ipconfig /all</code></li>
					  <li><code>ping [url]</code></li>
					  <li><code>tracert -h 15 [url]</code></li>
					  <li><code>nslookup [url]</code></li>
					</ul>
				  </li>
			  
				  <li><strong>Results:</strong> The results will be automatically saved in a <code>.txt</code> file on your desktop. The file path will be displayed, and the log will open in Notepad.</li>
				</ol>
			  
				<h2>üìÇ Example of Log File Location</h2>
				<p><code>C:\\Users\\tecon\\Desktop\\logs_app1_2025-05-09.txt</code></p>
			  </section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
